<h2>Web-standards alignment</h2>
<p>
  The platform primitives agree. <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_components/Using_shadow_DOM">Shadow
  DOM</a> scopes style and DOM but is <em>not</em> a JS sandbox; the
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/iframe">iframe</a> +
  <code>sandbox</code> is the one true origin/realm boundary; <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Reference/Elements/script/type/importmap">import
  maps</a> move loading to runtime but not trust; and
  <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/CustomElementRegistry/define"><code>customElements.define</code></a>
  is a one-shot global registration — the basis of the name-collision constraint a class-sharing scheme would have to
  solve. In all of them the <em>element/mount</em> is the unit that crosses; the <em>class</em> is the unit that doesn't.
</p>

<h2>Recommendation / impact on the decision</h2>
<p>
  <strong>Option (c) — &ldquo;extend #765 to compose FUI block classes at runtime&rdquo; — is struck.</strong> It is not
  a principled third path; it is the <a href="/backlog/707-reconcile-604-s-we-renders-real-fui-blocks-framing-with-the-/">#707</a>-forbidden
  import with extra ceremony (a verdict #791 already reached for source imports: &ldquo;#765's relax is runtime SDK
  only — never the #700 source import&rdquo;). #765's in-document mount of a <em>pre-rendered</em> component behind a
  shadow root is the correct, prior-art-aligned shape (the web-components / managed-mount pattern), and it
  structurally cannot give an app composable classes. So the WE artifacts that genuinely need block <em>classes</em>
  to wire behaviors — the two exercise apps — must live where those classes live: <strong>FUI</strong>
  (#812 Fork&nbsp;1, option a). The loader→background handoff demo, whose producer half exercises a WE-standard
  concern, decouples onto the escalation <em>contract</em> rather than co-running the moved impl (#812 Fork&nbsp;2,
  option d).
</p>

